                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9181.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-13T10:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 13, 1913—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>548. Department’s October 12, midnight. General Huerta last night said that no
                    violence whatsoever would be done to the deputies but that they must in many
                    cases stand trial for sedition and treason. He requested me to assure my
                    Government that they would be tried fairly by the civil courts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
